{
  "video_id": "IxndOd3kmSs",
  "title": "Meet the tardigrade, the toughest animal on Earth - Thomas Boothby",
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 7437.0,
      "end_time": 12818.0,
      "text": "Without water, a human can only survive for about 100 hours."
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 12818.0,
      "end_time": 18148.0,
      "text": "But there's a creature so resilient that it can go without it for decades."
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 18148.0,
      "end_time": 21458.0,
      "text": "This one millimeter animal can survive both the hottest"
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 21458.0,
      "end_time": 24708.0,
      "text": "and coldest environments on Earth,"
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 24708.0,
      "end_time": 28519.0,
      "text": "and can even withstand high levels of radiation."
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 28519.0,
      "end_time": 30420.0,
      "text": "This is the tardigrade,"
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 30420.0,
      "end_time": 33289.0,
      "text": "and it's one of the toughest creatures on Earth,"
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 33289.0,
      "end_time": 38049.0,
      "text": "even if it does look more like a chubby, eight-legged gummy bear."
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 38049.0,
      "end_time": 40749.0,
      "text": "Most organisms need water to survive."
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 40749.0,
      "end_time": 43059.0,
      "text": "Water allows metabolism to occur,"
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 43059.0,
      "end_time": 46080.0,
      "text": "which is the process that drives all the biochemical reactions"
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 46080.0,
      "end_time": 49249.0,
      "text": "that take place in cells."
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 49249.0,
      "end_time": 53409.0,
      "text": "But creatures like the tardigrade, also known as the water bear,"
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 53409.0,
      "end_time": 58069.0,
      "text": "get around this restriction with a process called anhydrobiosis,"
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 58069.0,
      "end_time": 61100.0,
      "text": "from the Greek meaning life without water."
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 61100.0,
      "end_time": 64728.0,
      "text": "And however extraordinary, tardigrades aren't alone."
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 64727.99999999999,
      "end_time": 65780.0,
      "text": "Bacteria,"
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 65780.0,
      "end_time": 68309.0,
      "text": "single-celled organisms called archaea,"
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 68309.0,
      "end_time": 69090.0,
      "text": "plants,"
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 69090.0,
      "end_time": 73269.0,
      "text": "and even other animals can all survive drying up."
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 73269.0,
      "end_time": 74671.0,
      "text": "For many tardigrades,"
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 74671.0,
      "end_time": 78571.0,
      "text": "this requires that they go through something called a tun state."
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 78571.0,
      "end_time": 80030.0,
      "text": "They curl up into a ball,"
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 80030.0,
      "end_time": 83620.0,
      "text": "pulling their head and eight legs inside their body"
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 83620.0,
      "end_time": 87000.0,
      "text": "and wait until water returns."
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 87000.0,
      "end_time": 89141.0,
      "text": "It's thought that as water becomes scarce"
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 89141.0,
      "end_time": 91501.0,
      "text": "and tardigrades enter their tun state,"
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 91501.0,
      "end_time": 94351.0,
      "text": "they start synthesize special molecules,"
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 94351.0,
      "end_time": 98041.0,
      "text": "which fill the tardigrade's cells to replace lost water"
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 98041.0,
      "end_time": 100430.0,
      "text": "by forming a matrix."
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 100430.0,
      "end_time": 103080.0,
      "text": "Components of the cells that are sensitive to dryness,"
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 103080.0,
      "end_time": 104111.0,
      "text": "like DNA,"
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 104111.0,
      "end_time": 105101.0,
      "text": "proteins,"
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 105101.0,
      "end_time": 106191.0,
      "text": "and membranes,"
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 106191.0,
      "end_time": 108580.0,
      "text": "get trapped in this matrix."
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 108580.0,
      "end_time": 111973.0,
      "text": "It's thought that this keeps these molecules locked in position"
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 111973.0,
      "end_time": 113631.0,
      "text": "to stop them from unfolding,"
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 113631.0,
      "end_time": 114868.0,
      "text": "breaking apart,"
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 114868.0,
      "end_time": 116931.0,
      "text": "or fusing together."
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 116931.0,
      "end_time": 120421.0,
      "text": "Once the organism is rehydrated, the matrix dissolves,"
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 120421.0,
      "end_time": 123887.0,
      "text": "leaving behind undamaged,  functional cells."
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 123887.0,
      "end_time": 128151.0,
      "text": "Beyond dryness, tardigrades can also tolerate other extreme stresses:"
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 128151.00000000001,
      "end_time": 129416.00000000001,
      "text": "being frozen,"
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 129416.0,
      "end_time": 131830.0,
      "text": "heated up past the boiling point of water,"
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 131830.0,
      "end_time": 133507.0,
      "text": "high levels of radiation,"
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 133507.0,
      "end_time": 137092.0,
      "text": "and even the vacuum of outer space."
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 137092.0,
      "end_time": 139221.0,
      "text": "This has led to some erroneous speculation"
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 139221.0,
      "end_time": 142562.0,
      "text": "that tardigrades are extraterrestrial beings."
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 142562.0,
      "end_time": 144150.0,
      "text": "While that's fun to think about,"
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 144150.0,
      "end_time": 147751.0,
      "text": "scientific evidence places their origin firmly on Earth"
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 147751.0,
      "end_time": 149772.0,
      "text": "where they've evolved over time."
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 149772.0,
      "end_time": 152503.0,
      "text": "In fact, this earthly evolution  has given rise"
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 152503.0,
      "end_time": 156322.0,
      "text": "to over 1100 known species of tardigrades"
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 156322.0,
      "end_time": 159653.0,
      "text": "and there are probably many others yet to be discovered."
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 159653.0,
      "end_time": 164783.0,
      "text": "And because tardigrades are so hardy, they exist just about everywhere."
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 164783.0,
      "end_time": 168463.0,
      "text": "They live on every continent, including Antarctica."
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 168463.0,
      "end_time": 171152.0,
      "text": "And they're in diverse biomes including deserts,"
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 171152.0,
      "end_time": 172283.0,
      "text": "ice sheets,"
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 172283.0,
      "end_time": 173182.0,
      "text": "the sea,"
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 173182.0,
      "end_time": 174143.0,
      "text": "fresh water,"
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 174143.0,
      "end_time": 175233.0,
      "text": "rainforests,"
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 175233.0,
      "end_time": 177242.0,
      "text": "and the highest mountain peaks."
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 177242.0,
      "end_time": 180913.0,
      "text": "But you can find tardigrades in the most ordinary places, too,"
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 180913.0,
      "end_time": 182904.0,
      "text": "like moss or lichen found in yards,"
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 182904.0,
      "end_time": 183693.0,
      "text": "parks,"
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 183693.0,
      "end_time": 184963.0,
      "text": "and forests."
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 184963.0,
      "end_time": 188403.0,
      "text": "All you need to find them is a little patience and a microscope."
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 188403.0,
      "end_time": 192323.0,
      "text": "Scientists are now trying to find out whether tardigrades use the tun state,"
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 192323.0,
      "end_time": 194364.0,
      "text": "their anti-drying technique,"
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 194364.0,
      "end_time": 196293.0,
      "text": "to survive other stresses."
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 196293.0,
      "end_time": 198683.0,
      "text": "If we can understand how they, and other creatures,"
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 198683.0,
      "end_time": 201852.0,
      "text": "stabilize their sensitive  biological molecules,"
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 201852.0,
      "end_time": 206043.0,
      "text": "perhaps we could apply this knowledge to help us stabilize vaccines,"
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 206043.0,
      "end_time": 211793.0,
      "text": "or to develop stress-tolerant crops that  can cope with Earth's changing climate."
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 211793.0,
      "end_time": 214214.0,
      "text": "And by studying how tardigrades survive"
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 214214.0,
      "end_time": 217373.0,
      "text": "prolonged exposure to the vacuum of outer space,"
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 217373.0,
      "end_time": 222195.0,
      "text": "scientists can generate clues about the environmental limits of life"
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 222195.0,
      "end_time": 224205.0,
      "text": "and how to safeguard astronauts."
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 224205.0,
      "end_time": 229164.0,
      "text": "In the process, tardigrades could even help us answer a critical question:"
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 229164.0,
      "end_time": 239164.0,
      "text": "could life survive on planets much less hospitable than our own?"
    }
  ]
}